{
  "stem": "10905.1",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But-- so we lived in Budapest.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then first came the laws that-- they-- they were not taking people yet, at that time, to concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But they were taking men to forced labor.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my mother  had three brothers.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The oldest one died someplace near Russia in a forced labor camp.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, I don't.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] mother's middle brother, younger brother, and my father were taken to a place call Garagn.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And don't ask me how to spell it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I think it's G-A-R-A-G-N.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they were there in the-- for a short period of time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My father being a physician, they needed physicians, so they let him come back.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we were together in Budapest.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, absolutely.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Absolutely.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Absolutely.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the law-- [BACKGROUND NOISE] You know, the-- the Aryan laws were put into effect.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was no walled ghetto.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But it's my perception that Jews lived-- had to live in a certain area.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "However, there were no walls and no dogs and guards-- I mean, nothing like that had in Eastern Europe.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] of course, jobs were scarce.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "However, Hungarian Jews are, you know, sort  of a strange mix of either assimilated or [NON-ENGLISH], the very, very, very, very, you know, orthodox.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And as a matter of fact, the-- the assimilated Jews used to call the very orthodox or Hasidic Jews 'Fins'-- Fin Poland, Fin Lithuania, Fin Latvia, [NON-ENGLISH], meaning 'from Poland,' 'from Lithuania,' 'from Latvia,' 'not from here,' You know, it was-- it was an expression.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I mean, the chief of police, once upon a time, Budapest, was a-- was a Jew and in a very, very high position.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So the Jews were very, very assimilated.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
